+
+// Williem R↔C local linear regression: at each pixel, sample the packed mip pyramid
+// at a coarse level (= tile-averaged means of R, G, R*G, R*R over ~32-64 src px),
+// fit the local map G ≈ a*R + b in closed form, then output (a*R + b, G, B, 1).
+// .r is the REMAPPED red -- it predicts what the green channel WOULD be at this
+// pixel given the local R->G relationship. Downstream disparity matching does
+// remappedR vs G, which works because both are now in the green-channel intensity
+// space (saturated red wrapper: raw R=255, raw G=30, remappedR ≈ 30, so the
+// matcher sees two near-identical channels for the same surface and can match it).
+//
+// matchTex here is bound to the PACKED (R, G, R*G, R*R) mip pyramid; g_propStride
+// is the mip level the caller picked for the desired tile size.
+float4 PSAnaRemap(VSOut i) : SV_Target
+{
+    float4 m = matchTex.SampleLevel(samp, i.uv, g_propStride);
+    float3 c = srcTex.SampleLevel(samp, i.uv, 0.0).rgb;
+    float meanR  = m.r;
+    float meanG  = m.g;
+    float meanRG = m.b;
+    float meanRR = m.a;
+    float varR  = max(meanRR - meanR * meanR, 1.0 / 65025.0);  // floor at one 8-bit step squared
